original: Jonsson, Algot Evald, komminister, Herrestad, f. 16/1/13 i Pdarne, Kalm. 1. — Stud :ex. i Sthlm 32, teol. fii. €x. 34, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt pTiästv. f. Linköp. stift 38. Pastorats-adj. i Lommaryd 38, kommin. i Herrestad ised. 42.
translated: Jonsson, Algot Evald, Vicar, Herrestad, born January 16, 1913, in Pdarne, Kalm [Kalmar county]. He passed his student exam at Stockholm in 1932, theology degree exam in 1934, theology candidate exam, practical theology exam, and ordained as a priest in Linköping diocese in 1938. He served as a parish assistant in Lommaryd in 1938 and became a vicar in Herrestad in 1942. He got married in an unknown year [not specified in the abbreviation].
